This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it deals with the placement of virtual machines on physical machines in a cloud computing environment. It may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as cloud computing heavily relies on network infrastructure. The paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category as it deals with optimizing the usage of hardware resources in a cloud environment. Additionally, it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it deals with the efficient usage of software resources in a cloud environment. Finally, it may also be relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it involves the development of algorithms for virtual machine placement.
